<div class="text-center">
    <h3 class="display-6">Michael Silver - Curriculum Vitae.</h3>

    <div class="summaryText">I bring over 25 years of experience in software development and technical leadership, with a recent focus on leading teams that design and build message-based, high-throughput, high-availability systems, primarily using .NET Core and cloud-hosted architectures. 
    </div>
    <div class="summaryText">My work spans hands-on development, system design, and team leadership across a wide range of technologies and industries. This experience has allowed me to adapt quickly, deliver reliable solutions, and guide teams through complex technical and organizational challenges.
        </div>

    <div class="summaryText"><strong>Core Strengths</strong></div>

    <div class="summaryBullets">
        <ul>
            <li>Extensive involvement in the <strong>full software development life cycle (SDLC)</strong>, from business analysis and system design through deployment, support, and ongoing enhancement.</li>
<li>Proven ability to foster <strong>open, collaborative work environments</strong> where team members are empowered to contribute ideas, challenge assumptions, and take ownership of outcomes.</li>
<li>Strong advocate for <strong>agile development practices</strong>, emphasizing collaboration, iterative delivery, code reviews, and comprehensive unit testing.</li>
<li>Passionate about <strong>learning new technologies</strong> and evaluating when and how they can be applied effectively to solve real-world problems.</li>
<li>Skilled at <strong>managing and exceeding customer expectations</strong>, balancing technical constraints with business goals.</li>
<li>Excellent <strong>communication, interpersonal, analytical, and troubleshooting skills</strong>, with a consistent ability to diagnose and resolve complex issues.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

